            <div type="apparatus">
                <listApp>
                <app n="1">
                    <note>Macalister (1945, 11) read:</note>
            <rdg source="MAC1945">
                <lb n="1"/><w part="F"><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown"/><unclear reason="faded">OVI</unclear></w>
                <w><unclear reason="faded">MAQI</unclear></w>
            </rdg>
                </app>              
                  <app n="2">
                      <note>Rhys (1898, 232) read:</note>
                      <rdg source="RHY1898">
                          <lb n="1"/><unclear reason="faded">CORBAGNI</unclear>
                      </rdg>
                  </app>
                    <app>
                        <note>According to Macalister (1945, 11), <q> there is a suggestion of MAQI preceded by what looks like ]OVI, the O being on the ground-line. But really the marks are so faint that it is possible to read almost anything into them : I was, however, quite unable to verify Rhys's suggestion, that remains of CORBAGNI were to be identified</q>. While ogham-like marks do appear on the relevant angle, neither of the previous readings are evident. It is possibly, as noted by Macalister, that some  of the inscription is beneath current ground level.</note>
                    </app>
                </listApp>
